China Evacuates Over 2,900 Citizens From Libya, Xinhua Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-02-23T14:34:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/china-evacuates-over-2-900-citizens-from-libya-xinhua-says-1-.html
More than 2,900 Chinese nationals
are being evacuated from  Libya  today, the official Xinhua news
agency reported, citing  China â€™s Ambassador to Tunisia Huo
Zhengde.  The Chinese nationals, mostly employees and their families
from Chinese companies in Tripoli and surrounding areas, will be
driven by bus to the Tunisian resort of Girba, Xinhua said.  China will send supplies including 10 tons of food, 4.5
tons of drinking water, 2,000 flashlights and some medicine to
Libya via Air China at 2 a.m. tomorrow as part of the
evacuation, the Ministry of Commerce said in a statement posted
on its website today.  The first group of 83 Chinese citizens left Libya for China
via Egypt, while 10 Chinese workers flew to Bulgaria, Xinhua
said in a separate report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
